ul.li:
Use the image-resolution CSS property:
        *[class ~= "topic/note"] {
    image-resolution:300dpi;
}

 Separate the image from the text and apply the width and height CSS properties only on
        the image, using the width and height properties. You could use multiple
          :before pseudo-elements for that, considering that the farthest content
        presented before the actual content of an element is matched by the :before
        with the highest number in the brackets:
        *[class ~= "topic/note"]:before(2) {
    content: url('note.png') ;
    width:0.5in;
}

*[class ~= "topic/note"]:before(1) {
    content: "Some text";
}
